# Loom

Loom is a literate programming framework. You write a document — prose and code together, in the order that reads best — and Loom tangles it, composing the code into real source files. The prose is half of the program: the half a person reads to learn what the code does and why.

This book is written in Loom, in the framework's own source, and it is the framework's only specification: the design notes that once sat apart from the code now live here, in the chapters that describe it, where they cannot drift. `loom weave` renders the book as the website you are reading — every chapter a page, its prose and its code side by side. Read it from the front. It starts with using Loom and then opens the machine, each part building on the one before.

