## Part VII — In the editor

A loom is several languages at once: prose, and code in whatever languages its sections use. This part gives each of them a real editor — syntax highlighting, errors, and completion, every diagnostic mapped back to the spot you wrote. Loom projects the document into a tree of virtual files, one language to a file, and hands that tree to the editor through a single plugin and a language server. Loom's own mistakes surface here too: a malformed tag, an anchor that resolves to nothing, shown beside the code.

::[The virtual-code projection](07-in-the-editor/the-virtual-tree.loom)

