## Part VIII — Languages as packages

Loom composes any language, so a language's editor support cannot be built in. It arrives as a package. This part is the contract such a package satisfies and the path it travels into a project. A service works not on a file but on a product — the code one section composed. The host lends each service its runtime, so the package ships thin. `loom add` installs it into the workspace store, a registry finds it by language, and the editor loads it on demand. TypeScript is the worked example, checked against the project's own configuration.

::[The Loom language-service contract](08-languages-as-packages/the-service-contract.loom)

