## Part IX — Loom builds Loom

The book closes where it began, with the fact that Loom is written in Loom. This part is the cycle that keeps that honest. The published tool builds the next release, never the in-progress source. Around the cycle sit the pieces that ship it — the command-line program, the bundles that fold each package into one file, the editor extension, and the release that publishes them all. It ends on the road still ahead.

